snippet: The signals, possibly from the “black box” flight recorders from the missing Malaysia Airlines Flight 370, will help narrow the search.
abstract: Australian search vessels have detected two more sets of signals that might originate from flight recorders from missing Malaysia Airlines Flight 370.

byline.original: By MICHELLE INNIS and CHRIS BUCKLEY
byline.contributor: Michelle Innis reported from Sydney, and Chris Buckley from Hong Kong. Kirk Semple contributed reporting from Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, and Keith Bradsher from Hong Kong.

lead_paragraph: The signals, possibly from the “black box” flight recorders from the missing Malaysia Airlines Flight 370, will help narrow the search.

headline.main: Two More Sets of Signals Detected, Australian Officials Say
headline.print_headline: Two More Sets of Signals Detected, Australian Officials Say
